The evidence with the title 'National debt interest payments dwarf other government spending ... ' says Nov 19, 2012  ... Taxpayers spend $ 220 billion per year on the national debt's interest — far more than on education or food stamps .  ... In 2012 , the U.S. will spend around $220 billion in net interest on its debt , according to the Congressional Budget Office — a figure that is expected to spiral ever higher in coming years . 
